re: https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/30529/commits/76fc51774e984c81512f2dd40dbaf42d2bbda18d#r1930837849

Definitely feel free to improve this. I think the most elegant solution instead of treating -debug=0 and -debug=none differently from -nodebug would be to treat them all the same and whenever any of these are specified just ignore any previous options.

Ability to reset the list and append new options afterward without having to choose one or the other can be useful when you have a wrapper script that passes some default options and you want to be able to pass more options to override them. FWIW, when I gave this suggestion to chatgpt it suggested:

```c++
auto last_negated = std::ranges::find_if(categories | std::views::reverse, 
    [](const std::string& cat) { return cat == "0" || cat == "none"; });

auto range_to_process = (last_negated == categories.rend()) 
    ? categories 
    : std::ranges::subrange(last_negated.base(), categories.end());

for (const auto& cat : range_to_process) {
    if (!LogInstance().EnableCategory(cat)) {
        return util::Error{strprintf(_("Unsupported logging category %s=%s."), "-debug", cat)};
    }
}
```

